{{More footnotes|date=May 2010}} '''Device tracking software''' is software installed in an electronic device that is capable of reporting the device's location remotely. Depending upon the software and the device on which it is installed, the software may obtain the location of the device by means of [[GPS]], WiFi-location, [[IP address]], or [[accelerometer]] logs, and it may report the address by means of [[e-mail]], [[SMS]], or other means.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bertagna|first=Patrick|title=How does a GPS tracking system work?|url=http://www.eetimes.com/document.asp?doc_id=1278363|accessdate=2010-10-26}}</ref>
Some device tracking software is sold as part of a subscription to a staffed service that will assist the device's owner to update police officers with the device's location.
