{{orphan|date=September 2012}}
'''Managed decline''' is a [[phrase]] that refers to the management of the decline (or "sunset") phase at the end of a [[Enterprise life cycle|lifecycle]], with the goal of minimizing costs or other forms of losses and harm. The concept originated in business where it referred to the management of companies and industries, but has since spread beyond to be used in other contexts.
Examples of managed decline include the handling of the [[textile]]s, [[shipbuilding]], [[coal]] and [[steel]] industries in [[North America]] and [[Europe]] in the 1980s,<ref>{{cite book|last=Coen|first=David and Wyn Grant, Graham Wilson|title=The Oxford handbook of business and government|year=2010|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=0199214271|pages=332|url=https://www.amazon.com/Handbook-Business-Government-Handbooks-Management/dp/0199214271}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Zan|first=Luca and Stefano Zambon, Andrew M. Pettigrew|title=Perspectives on Strategic Change|year=1993|publisher=Springer|pages=x|url=https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=AY3hxbpH7XQC&rdid=book-AY3hxbpH7XQC&rdot=1&source=gbs_vpt_read}}</ref> of the postal delivery services in [[Europe]] and the [[United States]] in the first decades of the 21st century,<ref>{{cite book|last=Enterprise and Department for Business|title=Modernise or Decline: Policies to Maintain the Universal Postal Service in the United Kingdom, an Independent Review of the Uk Postal Services Sector|year=2008|publisher=UK Stationery Office|isbn=010175292X|pages=59–60|url=https://www.amazon.com/Modernise-Decline-Policies-Universal-Independent/dp/010175292X/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1332102775&sr=1-1}}</ref> of the [[established church]]es in western Europe since the 1970s,<ref>{{cite book|last=Martin|first=David|title=On secularization: towards a revised general theory|year=2005|publisher=Ashgate Publishing Company|isbn=0754653226|pages=162|url=https://www.amazon.com/On-Secularization-Towards-Revised-General/dp/0754653226/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1332101964&sr=1-1}}</ref> management of Blackpool FC by Chairman Karl Oyston following the club's single season in The Premier League, and that of an individual's quality of life in their final years as they face old age or [[terminal illness]].
Decline can be managed through multiple means, including public or [[industrial policy]] efforts such as government provision of retraining.
